Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.55,0:00:03.62,Default,,0,0,80,,Goodness gracious, you're so...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.14,0:00:03.98,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)\an8}Ceske Orphanage
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.66,0:00:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times must you pretend to\Nrun away before you're satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.36,0:00:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do it again, you won't get dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.66,0:00:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear me, Milos?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.10,0:00:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.26,0:00:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Take your hands out of your pockets\Nwhen talking to someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.33,0:00:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.10,0:00:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,For real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.17,0:00:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It was that blonde girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.07,0:00:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw her on Dominican Street, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.18,0:00:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if she lives around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.01,0:00:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you keep following her?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.08,0:00:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.22,0:00:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In that case, let's find out where she lives...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.82,0:00:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and report her to the police.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.52,0:00:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And tell them that Mr. Grimmer didn't kill the director{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.06,0:00:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll prove his innocence.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.59,0:00:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Prove his innocence?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.66,0:00:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then Mr Grimmer will be off the hook.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.36,0:00:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's right.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.46,0:00:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll hold a meeting to come up with a plan.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.73,0:00:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Milos, hurry up and finish your dinner already.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.74,0:02:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the unlicensed orphanage where it first started.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.21,0:02:37.84,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(750,500)\pos(360,340)}The Cruelest Thing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.78,0:02:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The former director of 511 kinderheim\Nwas murdered by someone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.82,0:02:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids said that a blonde girl walked\Nthem right after it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.25,0:02:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He restarted his experiment here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.52,0:02:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike the one at 511 kinderheim...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.76,0:02:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,this one was to determine the\Neffects of love on the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.57,0:03:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you like to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.63,0:03:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we go in?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.70,0:03:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The police should have already removed any evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.84,0:03:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.74,0:03:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.25,0:03:12.50,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fad(250,250)}Mr. Policeman,\N Mr. Grimmer is innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.50,0:03:16.75,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fad(250,250)}Mr. Detective,\Nthe blonde girl is the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.05,0:03:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's those kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.85,0:03:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids from this orphanage must have\Ncome back and put these notes here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.06,0:03:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,"To Mr. Grimmer."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.20,0:03:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Milan Boucek.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.83,0:03:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a famous soccer player's card.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.37,0:03:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This must be something precious to the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I react?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.54,0:03:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In this type of situation, what should I feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.48,0:03:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My emotions were stolen by 511 kinderheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.69,0:04:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, I went to a special school\Nto learn how to express emotions...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.86,0:04:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But these types of situations are\Nthe most difficult to handle...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.60,0:04:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of expression would be appropriate here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.30,0:04:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How about paying those kids a visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.98,0:04:19.73,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\an8}St. Bardejov Orphanage
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.34,0:04:19.94,Default,,0,0,80,,You're Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.28,0:04:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I always hear a lot about you from the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.38,0:04:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They went out to play and haven't returned yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.49,0:04:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope they come back soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.56,0:04:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.36,0:04:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the children's diary...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.16,0:04:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it looks more like letters addressed to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.86,0:04:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mr. Grimmer, let s play soccer again."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.30,0:04:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mr. Grimmer is bad at soccer, so\NI'll teach him how to get better."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.61,0:04:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mr. Grimmer, come play with us again."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.41,0:04:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm smiling now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.71,0:04:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned how to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.45,0:05:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned how to make a smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.22,0:05:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm actually part of those kids' memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.90,0:05:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would they think of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.23,0:05:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they all like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.71,0:05:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They like me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.27,0:05:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought about...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.98,0:05:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,what kinds of emotions I should've felt...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.78,0:05:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,when my own child was dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.98,0:05:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I cry in this situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.69,0:05:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Just how much should I cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.29,0:05:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I scream at the top of my lungs?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.96,0:05:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Or should I clench my teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.33,0:05:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, I still don't know how I should have reacted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.80,0:05:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.84,0:05:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.44,0:05:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Antonin...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.14,0:06:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer, this is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.91,0:06:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Antonin?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.48,0:06:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We just got a message from the Ceske Orphanage...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.12,0:06:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Something bad happened...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.42,0:06:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down, Antonin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.09,0:06:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down and tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.16,0:06:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We found the blonde girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.46,0:06:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, we went looking for\Nher to find out where she lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.66,0:06:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Milos...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.77,0:06:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Milos disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.03,0:06:30.28,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)\an8}krumlov National Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.30,0:06:27.94,Default,,0,0,80,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.97,0:06:32.21,Default,,0,0,80,,The people who came to visit you were...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.61,0:06:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,a middle-aged gentleman...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.51,0:06:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a tall German...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.22,0:06:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and a Japanese man with long hair...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.75,0:06:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.45,0:06:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, wasn't there one more person you've left out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.89,0:06:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the nurse, there was a woman with\Nlong blonde hair who also came to visit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.77,0:06:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.00,0:06:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No, a woman didn't come to visit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.90,0:07:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the nurse was sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.61,0:07:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A very beautiful woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.61,0:07:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she was very beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.28,0:07:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But she was actually a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.65,0:07:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.42,0:07:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.22,0:07:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Milos.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.49,0:07:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Have we met somewhere before?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.79,0:07:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.50,0:07:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.93,0:07:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing, really...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.17,0:07:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You come around here a lot, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.81,0:07:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.78,0:07:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you looking for someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.25,0:07:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.78,0:07:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not come over here and have a seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.89,0:07:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I have some juice for you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.69,0:07:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... Are you moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.16,0:07:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.33,0:07:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a big bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.76,0:08:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's nothing in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.11,0:08:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Does your mother live around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.81,0:08:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.68,0:08:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you say you were looking for your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.88,0:08:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.25,0:08:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't know if she actually lives around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.38,0:08:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how are you going to find her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.42,0:08:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a picture of her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.46,0:08:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.26,0:08:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you don't know what she looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.93,0:08:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.26,0:08:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When I see her, I'll recognize her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.36,0:08:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody at the orphanage believes me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.53,0:08:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They all say there's no way I'd know...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.33,0:08:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'll recognize my mom when I see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.20,0:08:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.67,0:08:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.27,0:08:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom will recognize me when she sees me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.02,0:08:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What if she pretends that she doesn't\Nrecognize you when she sees you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.69,0:09:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you born because you were wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.50,0:09:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why were you abandoned?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.70,0:09:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't your mother abandon you\Nbecause she didn't like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.17,0:09:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,T-That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.27,0:09:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Being born really isn't that uncommon...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.68,0:09:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.91,0:09:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost everything in this world is meant to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.25,0:09:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In this world, a life born is nothing\Nmore than an insignificant speck...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.42,0:09:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and shouldn't even be counted as an existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.19,0:09:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Death is natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.73,0:09:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why are you alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.20,0:09:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it because someone wanted you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.37,0:09:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wanted you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.78,0:09:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your reason for living?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.78,0:09:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A girl with long blonde hair...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.99,0:10:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that would be Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.02,0:10:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.82,0:10:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this Anna live around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.19,0:10:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm pretty sure her apartment\Nis in the alley two blocks down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.83,0:10:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she's such a nice girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.24,0:10:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So polite, she never fails to greet me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.47,0:10:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.81,0:10:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she's such a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.01,0:10:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Always has a smile when she speaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.61,0:10:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what floor and room she lives in?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.25,0:10:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.79,0:10:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Third floor, that window.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.69,0:10:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If what the kids say is true...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.63,0:10:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and if Milos was really kidnapped by that woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.16,0:10:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and that Anna girl is really her, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.97,0:10:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Then if that person is who I think he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.41,0:10:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything will end here and now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.66,0:11:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They got away already?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.73,0:11:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did Milos go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Or was he kidnapped?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.41,0:11:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He was following the blonde girl\Nin order to prove my innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.98,0:11:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do now, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.65,0:11:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What expression should I make in this situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.96,0:11:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids got dragged into this case because\Nthey wanted to prove my innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.26,0:11:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids told us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.57,0:11:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That Milos usually wanders the streets of Prague...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.37,0:11:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.44,0:12:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted... to meet his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.54,0:12:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I... felt nothing, even when my own child died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.91,0:12:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, back when I was still\Nworking for the newspapers...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.65,0:12:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a female colleague told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.89,0:12:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that she liked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.32,0:12:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So I married her...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.33,0:12:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was taught that you're less\Nlikely to be suspected as a spy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.20,0:12:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're married.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.97,0:12:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She got pregnant...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.77,0:12:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and gave birth to a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.00,0:12:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then one day, my wife was out shopping nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.27,0:12:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When I entered my son's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.88,0:12:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,he was lying face down and had stopped breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.18,0:12:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave him CPR...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.58,0:12:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and called the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.22,0:12:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I did everything I knew I should do, without hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.66,0:12:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But he still died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.13,0:13:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,At the funeral, my wife broke down...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.06,0:13:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"How can you remain so calm?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.20,0:13:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Why can't you cry?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.34,0:13:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"You're always like this."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.97,0:13:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"That's how you treat me, too."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.14,0:13:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,"You're unable to love another person."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.21,0:13:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"There's nothing in your heart."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.01,0:13:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then my wife left me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.25,0:13:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to find Milos!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.86,0:13:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You said Milos was the child of a prostitute\Nin the red-light district...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.86,0:13:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,near the Czech border, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.40,0:13:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.73,0:13:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If the person who was living here is who I think he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.34,0:13:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think he'll let the boy live.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.44,0:13:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But he won't simply kill the boy either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.28,0:13:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If that person is who I think he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.01,0:13:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he'll put the boy through the cruelest thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.98,0:13:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,before killing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.09,0:14:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you keep going down this road, you'll be in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.43,0:14:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And my mom is somewhere down this road?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.59,0:14:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a very lively place up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.86,0:14:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be able to see my mom, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.37,0:14:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll wait for you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.44,0:14:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on ahead by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.17,0:14:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be able to recognize your mother when you see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.81,0:14:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And your mom will recognize you when she sees you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.24,0:14:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But if no one calls out to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.41,0:14:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that means nobody wanted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.22,0:14:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.02,0:14:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.69,0:14:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.94,0:14:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.97,0:15:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Cruel, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.43,0:15:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.33,0:15:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.30,0:15:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.17,0:15:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.10,0:15:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking for who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.94,0:15:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.24,0:15:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.37,0:15:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.84,0:16:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.24,0:16:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know your mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.52,0:16:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Where...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.38,0:16:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.42,0:16:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.09,0:16:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Technically, I know like...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.69,0:16:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,fifty of them here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.16,0:16:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why were you abandoned?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.43,0:16:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, my boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.77,0:16:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,My boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.84,0:16:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you, lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.37,0:16:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.88,0:16:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm, I'm looking for my mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.21,0:16:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind that, just let me hold you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.78,0:16:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with the kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.38,0:16:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that's your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.72,0:16:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.53,0:16:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't screw up like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.50,0:16:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though you're infected...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.70,0:16:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.70,0:16:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanna fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.93,0:16:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.17,0:16:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.64,0:17:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.64,0:17:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I already paid you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.04,0:17:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.44,0:17:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Do what your customer tells you to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.14,0:17:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.78,0:17:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A kid's watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.28,0:17:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.99,0:17:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,keep watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.72,0:17:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.76,0:17:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a teacher in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.86,0:17:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,At my school, I have a good reputation with the parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.80,0:17:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm an honorable man, and a wonderful teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.74,0:17:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A wonderful teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.48,0:17:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.18,0:17:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who wanted you?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.75,0:17:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.12,0:17:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Money...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.56,0:17:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sick, lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.39,0:17:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.66,0:17:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna die soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.20,0:17:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.66,0:18:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I just told you, because I'm gonna die soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.10,0:18:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Money, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.44,0:18:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I only have this much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.51,0:18:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Almost everything in this world is meant to die.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.85,0:18:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who wanted you?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.02,0:18:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What is your reason for living?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.44,0:18:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.05,0:18:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.86,0:19:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The red-light district ends around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.23,0:19:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of people saw Milos in the district.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.14,0:19:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we turn back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.84,0:19:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He may still be in there somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Milos!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.69,0:19:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Milos...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.60,0:19:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.77,0:19:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is all right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.70,0:19:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.61,0:19:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.58,0:19:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.21,0:19:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to prove my innocence...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.88,0:19:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You tried your best, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.52,0:20:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.89,0:20:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.64,0:20:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.04,0:20:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.48,0:20:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this how I'm supposed to feel, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.98,0:20:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it be better if I cried?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.55,0:20:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I was never taught...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.16,0:20:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,such complicated feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.64,0:20:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Milos?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.68,0:21:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.58,0:21:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you see back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.45,0:21:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What have you experienced?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.13,0:21:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Milos, listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.40,0:21:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.70,0:21:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.77,0:21:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There {\i1}is{\i} a reason why you were born!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.97,0:21:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You were born because someone wanted you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.78,0:21:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You were definitely...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.48,0:21:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You were definitely wanted by someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.85,0:21:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Definitely...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.84,0:22:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.07,0:22:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What I just said isn't wrong, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.28,0:22:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.25,0:22:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.82,0:22:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.48,0:22:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of expression do I have?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.49,0:22:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You're crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.18,0:22:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes... Gazing at what is known now in this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.53,0:23:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes... Your eyes believe in kindness...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.87,0:23:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Make it home... to your land of harmony...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.31,0:23:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Make it home... to your land of purity...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.15,0:23:53.57,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(750,0)\pos(360,340)}The Rose Mansion

